  "raw_html": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"broadcast-shape\">\n<span id=\"api-paddle-broadcast-shape\"></span>\n<h1>broadcast_shape<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#broadcast-shape\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\"></a></h1>\n<dl class=\"py function\">\n<dt class=\"sig sig-object py\">\n<span class=\"sig-prename descclassname\"><span class=\"pre\">paddle.</span></span>\n<span class=\"sig-name descname\"><span class=\"pre\">broadcast_shape</span></span>\n<span class=\"sig-paren\">(</span>\n<em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">x_shape</span></span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">:</span></span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">Sequence</span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">[</span></span><span class=\"pre\">int</span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">]</span></span></span></em>, \n         <em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">y_shape</span></span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">:</span></span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">Sequence</span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">[</span></span><span class=\"pre\">int</span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">]</span></span></span></em>\n<span class=\"sig-paren\">)</span>\n<span class=\"sig-return\"><span class=\"sig-return-icon\">→</span> <span class=\"sig-return-typehint\"><span class=\"pre\">list</span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">[</span></span><span class=\"pre\">int</span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">]</span></span></span></span>\n<a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/Paddle/blob/release/3.3/python/paddle/tensor/math.py#L4445\"><span class=\"viewcode-link\"><span class=\"pre\">[source]</span></span></a>\n</dt>\n<dd>\n<p>The function returns the shape of doing operation with broadcasting on tensors of x_shape and y_shape.</p>\n<div class=\"admonition note\">\n<p class=\"admonition-title\">Note</p>\n<p>If you want know more about broadcasting, please refer to <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"../../guides/beginner/tensor_en.html#chapter5-broadcasting-of-tensor\">Introduction to Tensor</a> .</p>\n</div>\n<dl class=\"field-list simple\">\n<dt class=\"field-odd\">\n           Parameters\n          </dt>\n<dd class=\"field-odd\">\n<ul class=\"simple\">\n<li><p><strong>x_shape</strong> (<em>list</em><em>[</em><em>int</em><em>]</em><em>|</em><em>tuple</em><em>[</em><em>int</em><em>]</em>) – A shape of tensor.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>y_shape</strong> (<em>list</em><em>[</em><em>int</em><em>]</em><em>|</em><em>tuple</em><em>[</em><em>int</em><em>]</em>) – A shape of tensor.</p></li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"field-even\">\n           Returns\n          </dt>\n<dd class=\"field-even\">\n<p>list[int], the result shape.</p>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p class=\"rubric\">Examples</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python notranslate\">\n<div class=\"highlight\">\n<pre><span></span><span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">paddle</span>\n\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"n\">shape</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">paddle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">broadcast_shape</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">],</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">])</span>\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"n\">shape</span>\n<span class=\"go\">[2, 3, 3]</span>\n\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"c1\"># shape = paddle.broadcast_shape([2, 1, 3], [3, 3, 1])</span>\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"c1\"># ValueError (terminated with error message).</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n</div>"
